title: Seldom's Tale 2
author: Marcus_Flaminius
pages:
#- 
§l      The Tale
          of
    Seldomshock
§r




§o            by
§r

      Seldomshock
#- §l



       Part II
#- My first stop on my journey was the Grand City of Lazuli. I dangerously took the Nether roads to get to my destination quickly. No danger came to me, as i arrived in the city intact. My first glance at the city immediately brought me to awe. Large towers 
#- marked my entrance. I was only a few steps into the city when I hear a raspy voice echo over the chat. "Who are you" The voice said. Me starteled that anyone was still in the city immediately dove into an alley. From behind cover I glanced in all 
#- directions to see where the voice came from. Responding the obvious "I'm Seldomshock" "Why are you here stranger" I heard as a response. I immediately gave all of my basic info about my mission. From behind some rubble of buildings emerged a man. We 
#- chatted back and forth, until I gained his trust. From behind him emerged an army. Startled I raised my sword in defense. My new friend quickly telling me to stand down explained the situation. He and his resistance crew were headed to an HCF boat to raid
#- it. Me with a young heart full of adventure decided a slight side-track was just what I needed. Walking through the rubble of the city I budged the leader(Lazer)'s shoulder and asked what happened to this place. He told me tales of a better time,
#- a simpler time. Now this city was part of the war zone. THe resistance fought with the savage HCF at every turn. Fighting for their city. This posed a question to me. If my home town were attacked would I put everything on the line to save it?
#- As twilight struck, we walkede onto the pier. There it stood a ship, a tint of read only compare able to the devils eyes themselves. WE quicly ascended the ladders and stepped on the deck. Besides a few chests nothing seemed out of the ordinary. The
#- others swiftly attacked the chests. Before I knew it 2 chests were down. Me taking this oppertunity to check the below deck hopped down the ladder. Below there were cannons a plenty. Taking no risks I dismantled every single one. I rejoined the rest back 
#- on deck to storm the cabin. Remembering I brought some TNT for sticky situations placed it around the door. Igniting the fuse everyone on board dashed towards the water with such speed you would've thought Mr_Twiggy himself was there. Following suit I
#- jumped as well. Entering the cabin brought us treashures a-plenty. Enough swiftness potions to make even Gordge drunk, and the gold stacks upon stacks. We piled it on deck handing it out equally. Everyone besides Lazer, me, and a few others were left 
#- looking around the ship. I took to the look out post to see my next route. Wouldn,t you know it but I found the perfect thing. A snitch. Quickly informing the others I started hacking at it with my newly found diamond hatchet kindly recieved from the
#- destroyed chests. After destroying it I found out the snitch belonged to NateMagic  a corrupt govoner of Lazuli cought multiple times of aiding the HCF. I asked if I could take the snitch to which the replied yes. I took the snitch with me to the museum, 
#- Definately to become a nice display.
#- 

